  "text": "The validation of models trained off-line does not guarantee a good performance in real situations, because of a fault or due to dynamic behaviour not represented in the training and validation data. The optimization should not be limited to the new parameter adjustment, but would evolve structure upgrading and refinement. For example, the aim of feature selection is to reduce the length of the training vector [CITATION_1] . An ideal assessment model would combine the statistical appraisal models with no cross-sectional error by identifying the over-and under-valuation of individual characteristics across similar properties. The last aspects will be concerned later in this paper.",
